=Russian Fairy Tales: Alexander Afanasyev
Wondrous Wonder, Marvelous Marvel: magical goose can be eaten and revived from bones, sticks to unfaithful wife and her lover
The Cock and the Hen: chain of barters to save choking rooster, not in time (bureaucracy)
The Fox Physician: fox disguised as doctor eats patient (hidden agenda)
The Fox Confessor: fox manipulates cock under religious disguise to eat him
Misery: misery tricks poor brother to spend all money, he traps it and becomes rich, jealous brother releases it and becomes poor (self-sabotage)
The Enormous Turnip: grandpa pulls out turnip with help of family and animals (unity is strength)
The Enchanted Ring: peasant receives magical ring, with it gets daugter of king, she steals ring and runs away
The Bad Wife: peasant tricks wife into pit, imp climbs out and works with peasant, later peasant scares imp away by shouting his wife returned
The Three Kingdoms: youngest son saves three princesses from underworld, his brothers betray him, he returns on bird
Emelya the Simpleton: fool spares pike, pike helps him to get princess and saves him at sea (be kind)
The Golden Slipper: dresses and slippers from magical fish (Cinderella)
The Just Reward: greedy officials ask peasant to share tsar's reward, he asks tsar for whip lashes (corruption)
Salt: foolish youngest son earns gold in land where salt was unknown, returns home with princess, his brothers betray him and giant saves him
Ivanushko the Little Fool: fool causes chaos, brothers want to drown him but he outwits them
The Miser: stingy merchant borrows kopek from poor peasant and later pretends to die to not return it (greed)
The Crane and the Heron: taking turns proposing marriage and rejecting and regretting (pride)
Alyosha Popovich: hero defeats giant with paper wings
Baba Yaga and the Brave Youth: youth tricks Baba Yaga and her daughters into oven
Prince Ivan and Princess Martha: prince frees wizard, wizard grants him magical strength, disguised prince saves princess by killing three dragons
The Cat, the Cock, and the Fox: cat warns cock against fox, cock disobeys and fox eats him (sometimes cat saves cock)
Baldak Borisevich: hero outwits and kills turkish sultan
